regen.absent_element: Ensuring comprehensive control sequences for units
regen.new_specification: The THEMAS system shall ensure proper control sequences to manage aborting or restarting operations of heating or cooling units to maintain desired system operations.

regen.absent_element: monitoring or alerts for queue usage
regen.new_specification: The system shall alert the operator when the queue for turn-on requests exceeds a specified threshold, indicating possible overuse or system imbalance.

regen.absent_element: transitioning from queued to active status when spots free up
regen.new_specification: The system shall periodically check if there are queued requests that can be transitioned to active status and process them accordingly.

label: When a request to turn off a heating or cooling unit is received, this process shall first check the LIFO queue and remove the unit-turn-on request from the queue if exists.
absence: action of checking the queue and removing the unit-turn-on request if exists when a request to turn off a unit is received
